canonical:
  title: 烟籠江水
  author: 姜希孟
  language: lzh
  text: 江空噴虛白匹練橫江中忽然聞欸乃知在蘆花叢
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 烟籠江水
  author: 姜希孟
  language: lzh
  text: 江空噴虛白。匹練橫江中。忽然聞欸乃。知在蘆花叢。
korean:
  title: 연롱 강수
  author: 강희맹
  language: kor
  text: |-
    강이 비어 허백을 뿜어 내매
    하얗게 바랜 베가 강 가운에 비끼었다
    갑자기 뱃사공의 노랫소리 들리나니
    갈대꽃 떨기 속에 있는 줄을 알겠다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_010_0010&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Mist Veiling River Waters
  author: Kang Hi-maeng
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The river breathes forth a hollow whiteness,
    A bolt of pale silk draped across the stream.
    Suddenly a boatman's song rises—
    And I know him nestled in the reeds.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'pale silk' (匹練) is a traditional image for mist or morning haze hanging over water in Chinese poetry, evoking both the ephemeral nature of the scene and the beauty of natural simplicity.
  - key: ''
    value: The boatman's song (欸乃) is an ancient Chinese expression for a ferryman's distinctive chant, representing human presence emerging mysteriously from the landscape.
